<p>We are equally concerned when studies talk about the high percentage of expenditure incurred by rural people towards non medical expenses like travel and accommodation, while seeking medical care. The following data might explain why this could be so. While an estimated 70% of population lives in rural areas, less than 30% of the Government hospital beds are in rural areas. Consequently, they would often have to travel to urban centers to get treated, which adds to their costs.</p>

